content: The set of natural numbers, with a lot of controversy over if it is including zero or not.
The set of integers, which includes all positive and negative whole numbers, as well as zero.
The set of rational numbers, which can be expressed as a fraction of two integers.
The set of real numbers, which includes all rational and irrational numbers.
The set of complex numbers, which includes all numbers of the form a + bi, where a and b are real numbers and i is the imaginary unit.
The set of quaternions, which extends complex numbers to four dimensions.
